      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(qqbot): validate direct media upload urls",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nValidate QQBot direct media upload URLs before they are forwarded to the QQ media upload API.\n\n## Changes\n\n- Reintroduced direct-upload URL preflight at the `MediaApi.uploadMedia()` sink.\n- Requires direct-upload URLs to use HTTPS and pass the existing `QQBOT_MEDIA_SSRF_POLICY` via `resolvePinnedHostnameWithPolicy()`.\n- Added regression coverage for allowed image/video/file URL uploads, non-HTTPS rejection, and SSRF-policy rejection before token lookup or QQ API calls.\n\n## Validation\n\nBehavior addressed: QQBot direct media URL uploads are validated before the QQ API request body is built.\n\nReal environment tested: Local Linux checkout with repo dependencies hydrated via `corepack pnpm install --frozen-lockfile`.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/qqbot/src/engine/api/media.test.ts`\n- `corepack pnpm format -- extensions/qqbot/src/engine/api/media.ts extensions/qqbot/src/engine/api/media.test.ts`\n- `corepack pnpm format:check -- extensions/qqbot/src/engine/api/media.ts extensions/qqbot/src/engine/api/media.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local`\n\nEvidence after fix: the focused Vitest target passed with 1 file and 5 tests; formatting and diff whitespace checks passed; autoreview returned no accepted/actionable findings.\n\nObserved result after fix: non-HTTPS and SSRF-policy-rejected direct-upload URLs fail before token lookup or `client.request()`, while allowed QQ/Tencent media URLs proceed to the upload request body.\n\nWhat was not tested: live QQ API upload with real credentials; broad `check:changed` or full-suite validation.\n\n## Notes\n\n- Security-sensitive exploit details are intentionally omitted from the public PR body.\n- AI-assisted.\n- `CHANGELOG.md` was not updated.\n- No agent transcript is included.\n",
